{
  "texts": [
    "Depending on the embedding model used, this compact representation enables researchers to efficiently process and analyze text data.",
    "By choosing an appropriate weighting scheme (for example, TF-IDF as in Seegmiller, Papanikolaou and Schmidt (2023)), researchers can also represent a document as a weighted average of the underlying word vectors, resulting in a fixed-length vector for each document.",
    "This allows for consistent and computationally manageable representations of text.",
    "By contrast, older methods like the BoW approach and its extensions represent documents as sparse vectors of a length equal to the size of the vocabulary or the union of all words (or n-grams) included in the documents, which can grow unwieldy for large corpora.",
    "The next discrete step in NLP goes beyond static word embeddings to vectorize entire documents while preserving their intended meaning."
  ]
}